                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-4976",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-4976] ReverseProxy forwards queries with more than urlmaxqueryparams parameters in net/http/httputil"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "ReverseProxy forwards queries with more than urlmaxqueryparams parameters in net/http/httputil"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "ReverseProxy can forward queries containing parameters not visible to Rewrite functions.\n\nWhen used with a Rewrite function, or a Director function which parses query parameters, ReverseProxy sanitizes the forwarded request to remove query parameters which are not parsed by url.ParseQuery. ReverseProxy does not take ParseQuery's limit on the total number of query parameters (controlled by GODEBUG=urlmaxqueryparams=N) into account. This can permit ReverseProxy to forward a request containing a query parameter that is not visible to the Rewrite function.\n\nFor example, the query \"a1=x\u0026a2=x\u0026...\u0026a10000=x\u0026hidden=y\" can forward the parameter \"hidden=y\" while hiding it from the proxy's Rewrite function."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-4976",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-39825"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-4977",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-4977] Quadratic string concatenation in consumePhrase in net/mail"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Quadratic string concatenation in consumePhrase in net/mail"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Pathological inputs could cause DoS through consumePhrase when parsing an email address according to RFC 5322."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-4977",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-42499"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-4980",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-4980] Escaper bypass leads to XSS in html/template"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Escaper bypass leads to XSS in html/template"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "If a trusted template author were to write a \u003cscript\u003e tag containing an empty 'type' attribute or a 'type' attribute with an ASCII whitespace, the execution of the template would incorrectly escape any data passed into the \u003cscript\u003e block."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-4980",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-39826"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-4981",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-4981] Crash when handling long CNAME response in net"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Crash when handling long CNAME response in net"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "When using LookupCNAME with the cgo DNS resolver, a very long CNAME response can trigger a double-free of C memory and a crash."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-4981",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-33811"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-4982",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-4982] Bypass of meta content URL escaping causes XSS in html/template"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Bypass of meta content URL escaping causes XSS in html/template"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-27142 fixed a vulnerability in which URLs were not correctly escaped inside of a \u003cmeta\u003e tag's \u003ccontent\u003e attribute. If the URL content were to insert ASCII whitespaces around the '=' rune inside of the \u003ccontent\u003e attribute, the escaper would fail to similarly escape it, leading to XSS."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-4982",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-39823"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-4986",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-4986] Quadratic string concatentation in consumeComment in net/mail"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Quadratic string concatentation in consumeComment in net/mail"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Well-crafted inputs reaching ParseAddress, ParseAddressList, and ParseDate were able to trigger excessive CPU exhaustion and memory allocations."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-4986",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-39820"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-5005",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-5005] Invoking key constraints not enforced in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh/agent"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking key constraints not enforced in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh/agent"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "The in-memory keyring returned by NewKeyring() silently accepted keys with the ConfirmBeforeUse constraint but never enforced it. The key would sign without any confirmation prompt, with no indication to the caller that the constraint was not in effect. NewKeyring() now returns an error when unsupported constraints are requested."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-5005",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-39833"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-5006",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-5006] Invoking agent constraints dropped when forwarding keys in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh/agent"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking agent constraints dropped when forwarding keys in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh/agent"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "When adding a key to a remote agent constraint extensions such as restrict-destination-v00@openssh.com were not serialized in the request. Destination restrictions were silently stripped when forwarding keys, allowing unrestricted use of the key on the remote host. The client now serializes all constraint extensions. Additionally, the in-memory keyring returned by NewKeyring() now rejects keys with unsupported constraint extensions instead of silently ignoring them."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-5006",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-39832"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-5013",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-5013] Invoking byte arithmetic causes underflow and panic in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking byte arithmetic causes underflow and panic in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "An incorrectly placed cast from bytes to int allowed for server-side panic in the AES-GCM packet decoder for well-crafted inputs."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-5013",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-46597"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-5014",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-5014] Invoking bypass of certificate restrictions in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking bypass of certificate restrictions in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "When an SSH server authentication callback returned PartialSuccessError with non-nil Permissions, those permissions were silently discarded, potentially dropping certificate restrictions such as force-command after a second factor succeeded. Returning non-nil Permissions with PartialSuccessError now results in a connection error."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-5014",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-39828"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-5015",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-5015] Invoking server panic during CheckHostKey/Authenticate in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking server panic during CheckHostKey/Authenticate in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "SSH servers which use CertChecker as a public key callback without setting IsUserAuthority or IsHostAuthority could be caused to panic by a client presenting a certificate. CertChecker now returns an error instead of panicking when these callbacks are nil."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-5015",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-39835"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-5016",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-5016] Invoking memory leak when rejecting channels can lead to DoS in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking memory leak when rejecting channels can lead to DoS in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "An authenticated SSH client that repeatedly opened channels which were rejected by the server caused unbounded memory growth, eventually crashing the server process and affecting all connected users. Rejected channels are now properly removed from the connection's internal state and released for garbage collection."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-5016",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-39827"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-5017",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-5017] Invoking client can cause server deadlock on unexpected responses in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking client can cause server deadlock on unexpected responses in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "A malicious SSH peer could send unsolicited global request responses to fill an internal buffer, blocking the connection's read loop. The blocked goroutine could not be released by calling Close(), resulting in a resource leak per connection. Unsolicited global responses are now discarded."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-5017",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-39830"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-5018",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-5018] Invoking pathological RSA/DSA parameters may cause DoS in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking pathological RSA/DSA parameters may cause DoS in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "The RSA and DSA public key parsers did not enforce size limits on key parameters. A crafted public key with an excessively large modulus or DSA parameter could cause several minutes of CPU consumption during signature verification. This could be triggered by unauthenticated clients during public key authentication. RSA moduli are now limited to 8192 bits, and DSA parameters are validated per FIPS 186-2."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-5018",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-39829"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-5019",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-5019] Invoking bypass of FIDO/U2F security keys physical interaction in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking bypass of FIDO/U2F security keys physical interaction in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "The Verify() method for FIDO/U2F security key types (sk-ecdsa-sha2-nistp256@openssh.com, sk-ssh-ed25519@openssh.com) did not check the User Presence flag. Signatures generated without physical touch were accepted, allowing unattended use of a hardware security key. To restore the previous behavior, return a \"no-touch-required\" extension in Permissions.Extensions from PublicKeyCallback."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-5019",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-39831"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-5020",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-5020] Invoking infinite loop on large channel writes in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking infinite loop on large channel writes in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "When writing data larger than 4GB in a single Write call on an SSH channel, an integer overflow in the internal payload size calculation caused the write loop to spin indefinitely, sending empty packets without making progress. The size comparison now uses int64 to prevent truncation."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-5020",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-39834"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-5021",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-5021] Invoking auth bypass via unenforced @revoked status in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh/knownhosts"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking auth bypass via unenforced @revoked status in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh/knownhosts"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Previously, a revoked 'SignatureKey' belonging to a CA was not correctly checked for revocation. Now, both the 'key' and 'key.SignatureKey' are checked for @revoked."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-5021",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-42508"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-5023",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-5023] Invoking VerifiedPublicKeyCallback permissions skip enforcement in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking VerifiedPublicKeyCallback permissions skip enforcement in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "Previously, CVE-2024-45337 fixed an authorization bypass for misused ssh server configurations; if any other type of callback is passed other than public key, then the source-address validation would be skipped."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-5023",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-46595"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-5024",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-5024] Invoking integer overflow in NewNTUnicodeString in golang.org/x/sys/windows"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking integer overflow in NewNTUnicodeString in golang.org/x/sys/windows"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "NewNTUnicodeString does not check for string length overflow. When provided with a string that overflows the maximum size of a NTUnicodeString (a 16-bit number of bytes), it returns a truncated string rather than an error."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-5024",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-39824"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "GO-2026-5033",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "[GO-2026-5033] Invoking pathological inputs can lead to client panic in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh/agent"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Invoking pathological inputs can lead to client panic in golang.org/x/crypto/ssh/agent"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "For certain crafted inputs, a 'ed25519.PrivateKey' was created by casting malformed wire bytes, leading to a panic when used."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2026-5033",
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "CVE-2026-46598"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
